body.description: At MAM we work with medical experts to anticipate your baby's needs from day one. Whether you’re using baby formula or breast milk, MAM bottles will support you every step of the way — the elongated nipple shape feels just like mom so you can easily switch between breastfeeding and bottle feeding. Our MAM Easy Start Anti-Colic Bottle is specially designed to minimize colic symptoms while feeding. The innovative vented base allows for an even drinking flow, helping to reduce colic for 80%* of babies. Each MAM Anti-Colic Bottle is self-sterilizing in three steps: fill in the base with 20ml of water, put the nipple on the base and close the bottle. Heat the bottle in the microwave for three minutes and it’s done! The bottle is made from BPS and BPA free materials, and the removable bottom makes clean-up a snap. It comes with a MAM Slow Flow Silicone Nipple for babies 0 months and older, accepted by 94% of babies**. *Field study, Austria 2011, tested with 73 mothers of colicky babies / Market research, USA 2010, tested with 35 mothers of colicky babies. ** Market research 2009-2020, tested with 1,572 babies.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Always gets the job done. Easy to wash, assemble and take apart. It reduces gas because of the vents as the base.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: We returned this size because our LO needed more formula than these offered but, these bottles saved the day and were one of the reasons that my baby easily transitioned between breast and bottle. The previous research and reviews did not lie. These bottles are loved by my baby as well as have many parent approved qualities. They are easy to clean (with a built in ability to sanitize). The vent function works to help prevent air within the bottle. You will still need to make sure that the milk is going into the nipple. Overall, the bottles are aesthetic as well as come in all of the variety you need to not purchase an abundance of bottling supplies.The only downfalls (if you will) are that the bottles do not heat well in a bottle warmer due to the thicker plastic base. You are not able to see the one ounce mark on the bottle itself, the included cap however is beneficial here.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These bottles are really good for newborns. So far it’s my daughters favorite. We have tried several but this one works best for us. The nipple is slow and these are also so easy to clean.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Good quality bottles we bought them because our baby liked the MAM pacifiers. Unfortunately we couldn’t get her to take this bottle or any other brand we tried. Eventually we gave up on bottles but these were nice quality and easy to clean.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best bottles ever
reviews.reviewText: My baby and I love these bottles. The only thing you need to be aware of: if you warm your bottles up in a pot with hot water- the water will get caught in the bottom section of this bottle so always be sure to turn the bottle over and get rid of the hot water that gathers in the bottom.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Keep up on the cleaning
reviews.reviewText: These were my favorite bottles when my twins were infants, you just have to keep up on the cleaning. Otherwise they get moldy because there is a part on the inside that acts like a seal that you have to take out and clean every single time. It also keeps the bottles from getting gross.They were really easy for the babies to hold because they were nice and wide and in my opinion are better than the skinny Dr. Brown’s bottles that are hard to hold because they’re a little fat arms. Can’t get that close together to hold them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best bottles I have ever used!!
reviews.reviewText: My son has a tongue tie and a high palate which makes every bottle we try leak from his mouth and make a mess with every feeding. We have tried 4 different brands. This is the only brand that he doesn't spill a drop. We use the 0 sized nipples for himHe ends up sucking up less air and having less colic symptoms. I'm literally throwing every single other bottle I own in the trash and ordering more. They are made of safe material for the baby too which is a massive plus as well!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fewer pieces, better cleaning
reviews.reviewText: Great if you’re breastfeeding and/or formula feeding. All the pieces come out easily. When putting back make sure the bottom white piece is put on well so water doesn’t drip. The bottle is chunky/wide than other bottles, baby will hold it good. Don’t let it discourage you on purchasing this.

reviews.reviewTitle: Las mejores mamilas que he comprado
reviews.reviewText: Son una excelente opción y de las mejores recomendaciones que me hicieron, fue para regalar. de todas las que recibió son las únicas que no le producen cólicos y el bebé se adapto rápido al chupete que tienen

reviews.reviewerName: No lo recomiendo se me daño la segunda vez que lo utilice

reviews.reviewText: Se adaptan muy bien a la boquita del bebé y casi no generan aire
Los puedes esterilizar gracias su sistema y los hace muy prácticos. El problema es que si le pasa algo de aire al bebé

Compre anteriormente un paquete en rosa después de utilizarlos dos semanas decido comprar estos en gris, calidad excelente, mi bebe desde su uso cero cólicos y menos aire. Habíamos calado otras marcadas pero la ajigaban o tenía flujo rápido la Mamila pero estos valen la pena.
